verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Our outward lips confess the name
All other names above;
Love only knoweth whence it came,
And comprehendeth love.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}We may not climb the heavenly steeps
To bring the Lord Christ down;
In vain we search the lowest deeps,
For Him no depths can drown.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}But warm, sweet, tender, even yet,
A present help is He;
And faith still has its Olivet,
And love its Galilee.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}The healing of His seamless dress
Is by our beds of pain;
We touch Him in life’s throng and press,
And we are whole again.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}The letter fails, the systems fall,
And every symbol wanes;
The Spirit over brooding all,
Eternal love remains.{/lang-eng}
